Hah hah! Evade that, (PG)!<br>
<br>
Anyway, as far as Featherlights, I haven't been able to aquire any myself, though I did have a FL axe when I was slash spec.  I have to assume it's pretty cool having two as you're likely close to, if not at, the 1.5s cap.  Sure each hit isn't gonna be devastating, but they're gonna start to add up (especially if they proc halfway frequently).  Also reactionary styles become VERY forgiving, while making it difficult for your opponent to use them.<br>
<br>
Your QBar sounds like it's set up pretty much the same as mine.  I have Dual Shadows, Concussion, Reflection/Hypno, and Flank/Shadows Rain.  I keep Back Crush on Qbar 2 usually so I can switch if I'm chasing someone, or coming up behind an unsuspecting caster <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .  Concussion btw is an attack speed debuff, not a snare.  When you look at the styles on the Herald if it says Hinders then it's a snare, Slows is an attack speed debuff.<br>
<br>
I'd have to say I recommend higher quality than the Featherlights, but they've sure gotta be fun (plus they look way cool).  I for one know just how hard it is for mercs to get fundage (been stuck at about half a plat for several months), so I would say stick with the Featherlights and maybe try for 100% weapons from Sidi raids and other similar raids. <p>Nirala HammahMastah<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
50 Hammah-wielding, chaos creating, caster bashing Merc of Gawaine. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lemonade@lighttanksofdaoc>Lemonade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/relic/Xid.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#000000>(4/10/03 7:39:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Hey Nirala! question plz..</span><hr size=1> Well I don't know if anyone else knows this about Needle Maces but if you can get a Weaponcrafter friend to make you one they sell back to merchants for exactly the same amount it costs to make them. So you could have them make you a 100% qual Needle Mace at the materials cost. Dunno if it is usable in left hand though.<br>
